  "decision_conditions": [
    "The proposed alteration to the existing roof at 248a Balmoral Drive, by reason of its size, scale, width, height and design would result in an incongruous, top heavy, disproportionate and bulky addition that would fail to harmonise with the architectural composition of the original, backland building and would be detrimental to the character, appearance and visual amenities of the street scene and the surrounding area by failing to respect the established context and urban grain. Therefore the proposal would be contrary to Policy BE1 of the Hillingdon Local Plan: Part One - Strategic Policies (November 2012) and Policies DMHB 11 and DMHB 12 of the Hillingdon Local Plan: Part Two - Development Management Policies (January 2020).",
    "The proposed alterations to the roof by virtue of its size, scale, bulk and proximity, would be detrimental to the amenities of the adjoining occupiers at 248 Balmoral Drive by reason of loss of privacy as well as 111 Lansbury Drive, by reason of overdominance, overshadowing, visual intrusion, loss of light and loss of outlook. Therefore the proposal would be contrary to Policies DMHB 11 of the Hillingdon Local Plan: Part Two - Development Management Policies."
  ],
